    <div class="pagecolumn">
      <div class="pagecontent">
        <p class="intro">Why Us? There&rsquo;s more to it than just really fast
          servers. Here&rsquo;s 10 of the many reasons to choose (mt) as your
          web hosting provider.</p>
        <ol class="numberedlist">
          <li>
            <p><strong>We never close.</strong> We never leave, and the lights
              are never off. We are a true 24/7/365 company. Call us at 3:00am
              New Year&rsquo;s Day - we'll be here. It&rsquo;s part of our <a href="/support/statement.php">Support
              Promise</a>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>We&rsquo;re affordable.</strong> When you truly consider
              the facts - when you add up all of the features - we undeniably
              offer more value than any nearest competitor. Sometimes you have
              to look beyond the price and consider all things such as quality,
              uptime, support and then features. There is a cost to &ldquo;cheap
              web hosting&rdquo; - don&rsquo;t let it burn you.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>We answer the phone.</strong> Our average hold time for
              technical support is below 2 minutes.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>We hire amazing employees.</strong> The talent runs deep
              within our organization. This means a better hosting experience
              for you. While working at (mt) Media Temple may be great, interviewing
              isn&rsquo;t all that fun. Our on-site (no book, no google) written
              competency tests take approximately 2 hours to complete (yes, we&rsquo;ll
              give you a Red Bull). Simply, we find, hire and train the most
              talented individuals possible and we work hard to keep them.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Serving since 1998.</strong> We&rsquo;ve been in the web
              hosting business for over 10 years (in  &ldquo;internet years&rdquo; that&rsquo;s
              something like 30 years!). We're not &ldquo;fly by night&rdquo; -
              we&rsquo;re not going anywhere. Our longevity and experience matters.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>The web needed a new hosting partner.</strong> In 2006,
              shared server technology died. The web changed, and so have the
              requirements of site owners. Traffic is up and traditional servers
              are buckling under the pressure. A new solution was needed that
              could handle overnight load spikes without costly reconfiguration.
              We had to re-invent web hosting. If you&rsquo;d like - go ahead
              and call us HOSTING 2.0.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Top tier data centers.</strong>
            Our data centers provide some of the highest level design and engineering features available in the world; surpassing uptime, security, cooling and power redundancy standards of most other hosting facilities.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>World's greatest designers.</strong> The world&rsquo;s
              hottest, most talented designers have trusted (mt) for years to
              serve their digital creations. Being the most critical demographic
              on the Internet, we believe this has strong merit.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>Innovation. </strong> Over and over (mt) Media Temple
              has been first to market with new technologies. Notably, we were
              the first hosting company authorized to host iASP for Linux, Macromedia&rsquo;s
              FlashCommunication Server, Zend&rsquo;s PHP Performance solutions,
              Six Apart&rsquo;s MovableType blogging software and now we have
              just released the world&rsquo;s most powerful, affordable utility
              computing hosting platform, <a href="/webhosting/gs/">The Grid</a>.</p>
          </li>
          <li>
            <p><strong>We rise to the challenge.</strong> Just like all complex
              systems, hosting services occasionally encounter problems. When
              something unexpected happens within our network that affects your
              websites, we immediately rise to the challenge and provide transparent
              status updates in real-time through our custom-built <a href="http://weblog.mediatemple.net/weblog/category/system-incidents/">incident
              manager</a>. Subscribe to the RSS feed for an incident to stay
              updated every step of the way until it&rsquo;s resolved.</p>
          </li>
        </ol>
      </div>
